The police, on Thursday, arraigned a 46-year-old woman, Janet Williams, in a Kubwa Grade 1 Area Court, Abuja, on charges bordering on criminal conspiracy and cheating. The defendant denied commiting the offences. The Prosecutor, Babajide Olanipekun, told the court that one Sunday Duniya of Kwali, Abuja, reported the matter at the Kubwa Police Station on May 31. He said the defendant and one other at large conspired and deceived the complainant to deliver 30 bags of charcoal to them. He put the value at N48, 000 and said the defendant refused to pay the complainant, adding that the offences contravened Sections 97 and 321 of the Penal Code. The Judge, Abdulwahab Mohammed, granted the defendant bail in the sum of N100,000 with one surety in like sum. He adjourned the matter to July 27, for hearing. (NAN).